{"type":"message","id":"a2aaaced","parentId":"2144695e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:53:11.876Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-24 17:53 GMT+8] 对，就填这个界面。\n按下面填：\nWebSocket URL：ws://127.0.0.1:18789\nGateway token：4ce285a836458029ef7e8775c14f0a8e1dc9a72415feaaa7\nPassword：不用填\n然后点 Connect 就行。\n连上以后你应该就能看到会话列表，再进 main。\n如果你懒得手填，也可以直接打开这个自动带 token 的地址：\nhttp://127.0.0.1:18789/#token=4ce285a836458029ef7e8775c14f0a8e1dc9a72415feaaa7\n如果你点了 Connect 之后还有报错，截个下一张图给我，我继续盯。\n你好了就在这里回我一下\n好，等我都修到一个像样的状态，就直接在这里回你。\n如果你觉得gpt 5.4 太消耗token就自己改成5.4 nano的模型\n好，我知道你的偏好了：如果后面我判断 gpt-5.4 太费，就优先自己切到更省的 5.4 nano / 轻量模型方案。\n好的\n即梦我已经登陆好了\n 这个飞书的发消息你没有回，这个修一下"}],"timestamp":1774345991868}}
{"type":"message","id":"9aa615b0","parentId":"a2aaaced","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:53:16.615Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"我先查清楚这个环境里“飞书发消息”应该走哪条通道，再修，不瞎猜。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0961688191b0a0c48a487cc007\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_o2KKUIEFn9gR2XXMf8BYK4qC|fc_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0c6fa881919eea5ff20576c055","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw channels --help","workdir":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw channels --help\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_MpZySQZoNga0VDvdPRCt7REc|fc_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0c71108191b4d7d10fabec3dcc","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw message --help","workdir":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw message --help\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_5Y4hTPBB8fUJgDnZGQOw7pDr|fc_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0c7118819193bd0681c0712e4d","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw directory --help","workdir":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace","yieldMs":10000},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"openclaw directory --help\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace\",\"yieldMs\":10000}"}],"api":"openai-codex-responses","provider":"openai-codex","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":448,"output":171,"cacheRead":71552,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":72171,"cost":{"input":0.0011200000000000001,"output":0.002565,"cacheRead":0.017887999999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021573}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774345991881,"responseId":"resp_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0894548191a3bb85dd264054e1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"a6728259","parentId":"9aa615b0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:53:18.367Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_o2KKUIEFn9gR2XXMf8BYK4qC|fc_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0c6fa881919eea5ff20576c055","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — I've seen your commit messages. We'll work on that together.\n\nUsage: openclaw channels [options] [command]\n\nManage connected chat channels and accounts\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add or update a channel account\n  capabilities  Show provider capabilities (intents/scopes + supported features)\n  help          Display help for command\n  list          List configured channels + auth profiles\n  login         Link a channel account (if supported)\n  logout        Log out of a channel session (if supported)\n  logs          Show recent channel logs from the gateway log file\n  remove        Disable or delete a channel account\n  resolve       Resolve channel/user names to IDs\n  status        Show gateway channel status (use status --deep for local)\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw channels list\n    List configured channels and auth profiles.\n  openclaw channels status --probe\n    Run channel status checks and probes.\n  openclaw channels add --channel telegram --token <token>\n    Add or update a channel account non-interactively.\n  openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n    Link a WhatsApp Web account.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/channels"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1740,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — I've seen your commit messages. We'll work on that together.\n\nUsage: openclaw channels [options] [command]\n\nManage connected chat channels and accounts\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help    Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add           Add or update a channel account\n  capabilities  Show provider capabilities (intents/scopes + supported features)\n  help          Display help for command\n  list          List configured channels + auth profiles\n  login         Link a channel account (if supported)\n  logout        Log out of a channel session (if supported)\n  logs          Show recent channel logs from the gateway log file\n  remove        Disable or delete a channel account\n  resolve       Resolve channel/user names to IDs\n  status        Show gateway channel status (use status --deep for local)\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw channels list\n    List configured channels and auth profiles.\n  openclaw channels status --probe\n    Run channel status checks and probes.\n  openclaw channels add --channel telegram --token <token>\n    Add or update a channel account non-interactively.\n  openclaw channels login --channel whatsapp\n    Link a WhatsApp Web account.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/channels","cwd":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774345998366}}
{"type":"message","id":"d1adaa74","parentId":"a6728259","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:53:18.371Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_MpZySQZoNga0VDvdPRCt7REc|fc_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0c71108191b4d7d10fabec3dcc","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — Running on your hardware, reading your logs, judging nothing (mostly).\n\nUsage: openclaw message [options] [command]\n\nSend, read, and manage messages and channel actions\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help   Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  ban          Ban a member\n  broadcast    Broadcast a message to multiple targets\n  channel      Channel actions\n  delete       Delete a message\n  edit         Edit a message\n  emoji        Emoji actions\n  event        Event actions\n  kick         Kick a member\n  member       Member actions\n  permissions  Fetch channel permissions\n  pin          Pin a message\n  pins         List pinned messages\n  poll         Send a poll\n  react        Add or remove a reaction\n  reactions    List reactions on a message\n  read         Read recent messages\n  role         Role actions\n  search       Search Discord messages\n  send         Send a message\n  sticker      Sticker actions\n  thread       Thread actions\n  timeout      Timeout a member\n  unpin        Unpin a message\n  voice        Voice actions\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\"\n    Send a text message.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --media photo.jpg\n    Send a message with media.\n  openclaw message poll --channel discord --target channel:123 --poll-question \"Snack?\" --poll-option Pizza --poll-option Sushi\n    Create a Discord poll.\n  openclaw message react --channel discord --target 123 --message-id 456 --emoji \"✅\"\n    React to a message.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/message"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1745,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — Running on your hardware, reading your logs, judging nothing (mostly).\n\nUsage: openclaw message [options] [command]\n\nSend, read, and manage messages and channel actions\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help   Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  ban          Ban a member\n  broadcast    Broadcast a message to multiple targets\n  channel      Channel actions\n  delete       Delete a message\n  edit         Edit a message\n  emoji        Emoji actions\n  event        Event actions\n  kick         Kick a member\n  member       Member actions\n  permissions  Fetch channel permissions\n  pin          Pin a message\n  pins         List pinned messages\n  poll         Send a poll\n  react        Add or remove a reaction\n  reactions    List reactions on a message\n  read         Read recent messages\n  role         Role actions\n  search       Search Discord messages\n  send         Send a message\n  sticker      Sticker actions\n  thread       Thread actions\n  timeout      Timeout a member\n  unpin        Unpin a message\n  voice        Voice actions\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\"\n    Send a text message.\n  openclaw message send --target +15555550123 --message \"Hi\" --media photo.jpg\n    Send a message with media.\n  openclaw message poll --channel discord --target channel:123 --poll-question \"Snack?\" --poll-option Pizza --poll-option Sushi\n    Create a Discord poll.\n  openclaw message react --channel discord --target 123 --message-id 456 --emoji \"✅\"\n    React to a message.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/message","cwd":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774345998371}}
{"type":"message","id":"1041e572","parentId":"d1adaa74","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:53:18.373Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_5Y4hTPBB8fUJgDnZGQOw7pDr|fc_070d3cbb0915198e0169c25f0c7118819193bd0681c0712e4d","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — iMessage green bubble energy, but for everyone.\n\nUsage: openclaw directory [options] [command]\n\nLookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for supported chat channels\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  groups      Group directory\n  peers       Peer directory (contacts/users)\n  self        Show the current account user\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw directory self --channel slack\n    Show the connected account identity.\n  openclaw directory peers list --channel slack --query \"alice\"\n    Search contact/user IDs by name.\n  openclaw directory groups list --channel discord\n    List available groups/channels.\n  openclaw directory groups members --channel discord --group-id <id>\n    List members for a specific group.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/directory"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1729,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — iMessage green bubble energy, but for everyone.\n\nUsage: openclaw directory [options] [command]\n\nLookup contact and group IDs (self, peers, groups) for supported chat channels\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  groups      Group directory\n  peers       Peer directory (contacts/users)\n  self        Show the current account user\n\nExamples:\n  openclaw directory self --channel slack\n    Show the connected account identity.\n  openclaw directory peers list --channel slack --query \"alice\"\n    Search contact/user IDs by name.\n  openclaw directory groups list --channel discord\n    List available groups/channels.\n  openclaw directory groups members --channel discord --group-id <id>\n    List members for a specific group.\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/directory","cwd":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774345998371}}
