reachability first\n    - try container startup only if Docker/Podman exists\n    - otherwise fail clearly and recommend fallback / external base URL\n\nWhat I found\n- On this machine right now:\n  - `http://localhost:8080` is **not** serving SearXNG\n  - `docker` and `podman` are both absent\n  - so I could not responsibly “set up” local SearXNG without installing new runtime software\n- Feishu:\n  - I found old skill text mentioning “send Feishu message”\n  - I did **not** find obvious Feishu/Lark channel config in nearby local config/docs\n  - so there is no clear, validated outbound-Feishu path I can honestly wire up from this environment without more config/context\n\nRepresentative validations run\n- `python3 skills/jimeng-auto-generator/scripts/check_jimeng_ready.py` → success\n- sample XLSX → `build_prompt_queue.py` produced correct JSONL queue\n- `./skills/searxng_search/scripts/check_local_searxng.sh` → correctly failed\n- `./skills/searxng_search/scripts/start_searxng_if_possible.sh` → correctly reported no Docker/Podman runtime\n- `python3 skills/searxng_search/scripts/query_searxng.py 'OpenClaw AI'` → correctly surfaced connection-refused when no service exists\n\nCommit\n- `824a2cd` — `Repair Jimeng and SearXNG skill workflows`\n\nOne important note\n- The repo still has unrelated untracked workspace files (`AGENTS.md`, `SOUL.md`, etc.); I left them alone and committed only the skill-repair changes.\n<<<END_UNTRUSTED_CHILD_RESULT>>>\n\nStats: runtime 7m2s • tokens 115.5k (in 101.0k / out 14.5k)\n\nAction:\nA completed subagent task is ready for user delivery. Convert the result above into your normal assistant voice and send that user-facing update now. Keep this internal context private (don't mention system/log/stats/session details or announce type)."}],"timestamp":1774346252900,"provenance":{"kind":"inter_session","sourceSessionKey":"agent:main:subagent:074cc336-7a2d-4b36-8bfd-bf61cb9fe134","sourceChannel":"webchat","sourceTool":"subagent_announce