{"type":"compaction","id":"8e126132","parentId":"41353a44","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:39:49.155Z","summary":"## Goal\n1. **Skills installation & repair**: Install and fix workspace skills (jimeng-auto-generator, news-aggregator, searxng_search, video-*, etc.) making them practically runnable.\n2. **Infrastructure provisioning**: Install Docker Desktop and Python 3.11 on the Mac to enable local SearXNG and skill dependencies.\n3. **OpenClaw stability / self-healing**: Design and implement a multi-layer stability architecture for the mac mini OpenClaw deployment, using Tencent Cloud server as remote repair endpoint. Execute in phases.\n4. **Jimeng stable batch submit loop**: Push from current semi-auto state to stable unattended submit闭环.\n\n## Constraints & Preferences\n- User authorizes autonomous installation without asking for confirmation (\"统一安装，以后你不用问我\")\n- Report progress every 10 minutes via Feishu into this chat (in addition to updating `STATUS.md`)\n- User prefers GPT-5.4-nano if token usage gets high\n- Feishu messaging via `openclaw message send --channel feishu --target ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356`\n- Do not perform destructive actions; prefer direct local fixes and validation\n- User wants to see real-time work status via `~/Desktop/STATUS.md`\n- For Jimeng: keep page stable, provide 3-5 real prompts or small xlsx for batch submit testing\n- User is exercising; wants to monitor progress hands-free via the chat\n\n## Progress\n### Done\n- [x] Installed skills from `~/Desktop/openclaw-skills-main/skills/` → `/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`\n- [x] Fixed all 7 SKILL.md files (removed bad metadata format, rewrote honest descriptions)\n- [x] Made `jimeng-auto-generator` recognized (fixed SKILL.md format, added `requirements.txt`)\n- [x] Installed Python deps: `flask`, `openpyxl` → Flask 3.1.3, openpyxl 3.1.5\n- [x] Started `jimeng-auto-generator` Flask app on `http://127.0.0.1:5001` (validated: serves, parses xlsx, generates queues)\n- [x] Added `scripts/parse_xlsx_prompts.py`, `scripts/check_browser_env.sh`, `scripts/build_prompt_queue.py`, `scripts/check_jimeng_ready.py`\n- [x] Added `references/browser-semi-auto.md` with validated `browser.snapshot(refs=\"aria\")` + `browser.act` pattern\n- [x] Verified Jimeng tab exists, textbox detectable, click/type actions work\n- [x] Rewrote `news-aggregator` and `searxng_search` SKILL.md with proper fallback logic\n- [x] Fixed `searxng_search` scripts: `query_searxng.py`, `check_local_searxng.sh`, `start_searxng_if_possible.sh`\n- [x] Installed Python 3.11 (Homebrew) → `/opt/homebrew/bin/python3.11`, version 3.11.15\n- [x] Docker Desktop already present (`/Applications/Docker.app`), `docker --version` = 29.3.0\n- [x] Pulled and started SearXNG container: `docker run -d --name openclaw-searxng -p 8080:8080 -e BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/ searxng/searxng:latest`\n- [x] **SearXNG container confirmed running**: logs show `Listening at: http://:::8080`, worker PID 930 spawned, service alive\n- [x] Git commits: `0cfaac6`, `9b3d02f`, `8c2d630`, `824a2cd`\n- [x] Fixed Feishu outbound messaging (correct usage: `openclaw message send --channel feishu --target ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356`)\n- [x] Read `healthcheck/SKILL.md` for AI ops reference\n- [x] **Completed OpenClaw self-healing architecture design** via subagent (`design-openclaw-self-heal`): 4-layer architecture defined (launchd → local watchdog → Tencent Cloud monitor → human escalation), escalation levels defined, self-heal vs. cannot-self-heal lists produced\n- [x] Confirmed OpenClaw is already a macOS LaunchAgent; gateway bound to `127.0.0.1:18789`\n- [x] Confirmed `openclaw cron` is available for watchdog scheduling\n- [x] Confirmed `openclaw health --json`, `openclaw gateway status`, `openclaw status --deep` are available probe commands\n- [x] Created `~/Desktop/STATUS.md` — real-time work status file on desktop for user to monitor progress\n- [x] Confirmed Jimeng page is logged in, textbox detectable, click/type works, prompt extraction and queue building functional\n\n### In Progress\n- [ ] **SearXNG query JSON打通**: Container is up and listening, but `curl localhost:8080/search?q=test&format=json` returns HTML instead of JSON — needs query format/config fix\n- [ ] **Local watchdog 落地**: Strategy defined (retry-once then restart), `openclaw cron` confirmed usable — need to write actual script/commands and wire to scheduling\n- [ ] **Jimeng stable batch submit**: Base layer done (login OK, page OK, queue OK), missing: stable batch loop with ref-resilience, failure retry, graceful degradation\n\n### Blocked\n- Tailscale conflicts with user's existing VPN (when Tailscale on, VPN drops) — reverse SSH recommended as primary remote bridge solution instead\n- Security audit criticals found (Feishu `groupPolicy=open`, broad runtime/fs/elevated exposure) — should be fixed before expanding automation authority\n\n## Key Decisions\n- **Install-first approach authorized**: User gave blanket approval for installing Docker, Python deps without asking\n- **Honest skill boundaries**: Skills rewritten to accurately describe what they can and cannot do (no false \"fully automatic\" claims)\n- **Python 3.11 via Homebrew**: Installed as `python@3.11` rather than replacing system python3\n- **Docker Desktop pre-existing**: Confirmed `/Applications/Docker.app` was already installed\n- **SearXNG container**: Running with `BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/`, listening on `:::8080`\n- **Jimeng auto-generator**: Reclassified as \"honest semi-auto prompt extractor + queue builder\", NOT fully automated\n- **Feishu outbound**: Correct command is `openclaw message send --channel feishu --target ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356`\n- **Remote repair bridge: reverse SSH preferred over Tailscale**: User's Tailscale conflicts with existing VPN; reverse SSH tunnel from Mac → Tencent Cloud is recommended as simpler, non-conflicting alternative\n- **Watchdog strategy**: fail-once → retry 30-60s → fail-twice → `openclaw gateway restart` → probe again → still bad → alert and stop escalation (avoids restart storm)\n- **Phase order**: Keep gateway loopback-only → add local watchdog → fix security criticals → then add Tencent Cloud bridge\n- **Jimeng testing needs**: User to keep Jimeng page stable (no switching tabs/pages), provide 3-5 real prompts or small xlsx for batch submit validation\n\n## Next Steps\n1. **SearXNG**: Fix query format/config so `curl \"http://localhost:8080/search?q=test&format=json\"` returns valid JSON; verify `searxng_search` skill can query successfully\n2. **Local watchdog**: Write watchdog script using `openclaw health --json` probe with retry/restart logic, wire to `openclaw cron` scheduling; produce first executable version\n3. **Jimeng batch submit**: With 3-5 test prompts from user, validate stable batch submit loop with retry/ref-resilience\n4. **Remote repair bridge**: Design reverse SSH tunnel from Mac to Tencent Cloud as Tailscale-free alternative; get user's confirmation on connectivity method\n5. **Security criticals**: Address Feishu `groupPolicy=open` and broad exposure findings before expanding automation scope\n6. **Report**: Continue 10-minute progress updates to this chat + maintain `~/Desktop/STATUS.md`\n\n## Critical Context\n- **Workspace path**: `/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace/skills/`\n- **Desktop STATUS.md**: `/Users/palpet/Desktop/STATUS.md`\n- **SearXNG container**: name=`openclaw-searxng`, port `8080:8080`, logs confirm service listening\n- **Jimeng app**: running on `http://127.0.0.1:5001` (Flask/PID confirmed)\n- **Jimeng page confirmed live**: `https://jimeng.jianying.com/ai-tool/generate?type=image&workspace=0`; textbox ref detectable via `compact=false` snapshot; submit via `browser.act(press Enter)`\n- **User's Tencent Cloud server**: available for remote repair/connectivity; details not yet provided\n- **User's existing VPN**: conflicts with Tailscale; reverse SSH recommended as workaround\n- **OpenClaw self-healing architecture**: 4 layers (launchd → local watchdog → Tencent Cloud monitor → human escalation), Phase 1 now executing (local watchdog first)\n- **Model**: `openai-codex/gpt-5.4` (user jokingly referred to this as \"全世界最聪明的gpt5.4\")\n- **User context**: is exercising, wants hands-free monitoring of progress via chat\n\n## Open TODOs\n1. Confirm SearXNG returns JSON on query (fix container config/query format)\n2. Wire Jimeng queue → browser submit loop with retry/ref-resilient logic\n3. Write and deploy local watchdog script via `openclaw cron`\n4. Confirm Tencent Cloud connectivity method (reverse SSH preferred)\n5. Fix Feishu security audit criticals (`groupPolicy=open`, broad exposure)\n6. Validate Jimeng batch submit with 3-5 real prompts from user\n\n## Decisions\n- **Skills installed to**: `/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace/skills/` (workspace-level, not bundled)\n- **Python 3.11 via Homebrew**: `/opt/homebrew/bin/python3.11`, version 3.11.15\n- **SearXNG container**: `docker run -d --name openclaw-searxng -p 8080:8080 -e BASE_URL=http://localhost:8080/ searxng/searxng:latest`\n- **Watchdog strategy**: retry-once after 30-60s → second failure triggers `openclaw gateway restart` → still bad → alert and stop\n- **Remote bridge: reverse SSH over Tailscale**: Tailscale conflicts with existing VPN; reverse SSH from Mac → Tencent avoids routing conflicts\n- **Phase 1 execution**: Local watchdog is the first implementation priority, then remote bridge\n\n## Constraints/Rules\n- No destructive actions\n- Report every ≤10 minutes via this chat + maintain `~/Desktop/STATUS.md`\n- User prefers `gpt-5.4-nano` if token consumption is high\n- All installs/actions authorized without per-step confirmation\n- Keep workspace files under `/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace/`\n- Require explicit approval before any state-changing action on host\n- Do not modify remote access settings without confirming how user connects\n- Prefer reversible, staged changes w