{"type":"message","id":"42ddca4e","parentId":"5c5f35ee","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:34.606Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, no existing cron jobs. Now let me add the watchdog cron job. The strategy from the design doc says:\n- Check every 5 minutes\n- But with the \"fail once → wait 30s → fail twice → restart → check\" logic built into the script\n\nLet me add the cron job now. I'll use `openclaw cron add` or whatever the command is.","thinkingSignature":"00f8834c404f85e2774c7f1ad445391ec969d233e2b924279109ff406a3945bc"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2alhvg1j2727_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron --help 2>&1 | head -30","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":40929,"output":127,"cacheRead":16722,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":57778,"cost":{"input":0.0122787,"output":0.0001524,"cacheRead":0.0010033199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01343442}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359749944,"responseId":"0611c7c6b4f395306ed5516c3f64c57a"}}
{"type":"message","id":"99cef9cb","parentId":"42ddca4e","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:34.916Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_2alhvg1j2727_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — Less clicking, more shipping, fewer \"where did that file go\" moments.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron [options] [command]\n\nManage cron jobs (via Gateway)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add         Add a cron job\n  disable     Disable a cron job\n  edit        Edit a cron job (patch fields)\n  enable      Enable a cron job\n  help        Display help for command\n  list        List cron jobs\n  rm          Remove a cron job\n  run         Run a cron job now (debug)\n  runs        Show cron run history (JSONL-backed)\n  status      Show cron scheduler status\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/cron\nUpgrade tip: run `openclaw doctor --fix` to normalize legacy cron job storage."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":301,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — Less clicking, more shipping, fewer \"where did that file go\" moments.\n\nUsage: openclaw cron [options] [command]\n\nManage cron jobs (via Gateway)\n\nOptions:\n  -h, --help  Display help for command\n\nCommands:\n  add         Add a cron job\n  disable     Disable a cron job\n  edit        Edit a cron job (patch fields)\n  enable      Enable a cron job\n  help        Display help for command\n  list        List cron jobs\n  rm          Remove a cron job\n  run         Run a cron job now (debug)\n  runs        Show cron run history (JSONL-backed)\n  status      Show cron scheduler status\n\nDocs: https://docs.openclaw.ai/cli/cron\nUpgrade tip: run `openclaw doctor --fix` to normalize legacy cron job storage.","cwd":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359754915}}
{"type":"message","id":"bf60a3e0","parentId":"99cef9cb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:37.159Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can use `openclaw cron add`. Let me see the add options.","thinkingSignature":"05d9770baeef6c48378ec4a793667c2848da1aa0db7901bcb56a87b714826b94"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8voh2jy5rpjm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add --help 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":41262,"output":63,"cacheRead":16722,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":58047,"cost":{"input":0.0123786,"output":0.0000756,"cacheRead":0.0010033199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01345752}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359754916,"responseId":"0611c7cbdf96857c521a3dc15c5e90ac"}}
{"type":"message","id":"f17d2635","parentId":"bf60a3e0","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:37.472Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8voh2jy5rpjm_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Announce summary to a chat (subagent-style) (default:\n                         false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO with offset, or +duration). Use\n                         --tz for offset-less datetimes\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Announces a summary to a\n                         chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable announce delivery and skip main-session summary\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh)\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":307,"aggregated":"🦞 OpenClaw 2026.3.23-2 (7ffe7e4) — If it works, it's automation; if it breaks, it's a \"learning opportunity.\"\n\nUsage: openclaw cron add|create [options]\n\nAdd a cron job\n\nOptions:\n  --account <id>         Channel account id for delivery (multi-account setups)\n  --agent <id>           Agent id for this job\n  --announce             Announce summary to a chat (subagent-style) (default:\n                         false)\n  --at <when>            Run once at time (ISO with offset, or +duration). Use\n                         --tz for offset-less datetimes\n  --best-effort-deliver  Do not fail the job if delivery fails (default: false)\n  --channel <channel>    Delivery channel (last) (default: \"last\")\n  --cron <expr>          Cron expression (5-field or 6-field with seconds)\n  --delete-after-run     Delete one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --deliver              Deprecated (use --announce). Announces a summary to a\n                         chat.\n  --description <text>   Optional description\n  --disabled             Create job disabled (default: false)\n  --every <duration>     Run every duration (e.g. 10m, 1h)\n  --exact                Disable cron staggering (set stagger to 0) (default:\n                         false)\n  --expect-final         Wait for final response (agent) (default: false)\n  -h, --help             Display help for command\n  --json                 Output JSON (default: false)\n  --keep-after-run       Keep one-shot job after it succeeds (default: false)\n  --light-context        Use lightweight bootstrap context for agent jobs\n                         (default: false)\n  --message <text>       Agent message payload\n  --model <model>        Model override for agent jobs (provider/model or alias)\n  --name <name>          Job name\n  --no-deliver           Disable announce delivery and skip main-session summary\n  --session <target>     Session target (main|isolated)\n  --session-key <key>    Session key for job routing (e.g.\n                         agent:my-agent:my-session)\n  --stagger <duration>   Cron stagger window (e.g. 30s, 5m)\n  --system-event <text>  System event payload (main session)\n  --thinking <level>     Thinking level for agent jobs\n                         (off|minimal|low|medium|high|xhigh)\n  --timeout <ms>         Timeout in ms (default: \"30000\")\n  --timeout-seconds <n>  Timeout seconds for agent jobs\n  --to <dest>            Delivery destination (E.164, Telegram chatId, or\n                         Discord channel/user)\n  --token <token>        Gateway token (if required)\n  --tz <iana>            Timezone for cron expressions (IANA) (default: \"\")\n  --url <url>            Gateway WebSocket URL (defaults to gateway.remote.url\n                         when configured)\n  --wake <mode>          Wake mode (now|next-heartbeat) (default: \"now\")","cwd":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359757471}}
{"type":"message","id":"5866bd84","parentId":"f17d2635","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:49.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I can add the cron job. The watchdog script needs to run periodically, say every 5 minutes. The script itself handles the fail-once → retry → fail-twice → restart logic.\n\nLet me add the cron job:\n- Every 5 minutes\n- Running the watchdog script\n- No need for agent/announce delivery\n\nI should use `--every 5m` and the command would be the script path. But wait - cron jobs in OpenClaw work by sending a message to an agent. The script approach might not work directly since cron jobs are agent messages, not shell commands.\n\nActually, let me re-read the cron docs. Looking at the options, it seems like cron jobs are more about triggering agent messages rather than running arbitrary shell scripts. \n\nSo I need to either create a lightweight agent just for the watchdog that receives periodic cron messages and executes the shell script, or find a way to run the script through the cron system. The cron job would send a message to an agent, which then runs the watchdog script. Let me set up a cron job that triggers an agent task to execute the watchdog script every 5 minutes. Looking at the cron options more carefully, I think the right approach is to create a simple agent job that handles the watchdog logic, since OpenClaw's cron is really designed around agent message delivery rather than direct script execution. Let me structure this as a cron job that sends a lightweight message to trigger the watchdog behavior.","thinkingSignature":"b855950c8b9aaf1437867c99c79abe00c7ff045cc4ea32e1f0aa9173fc9a9c4a"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ngdkfzpi8650_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"openclaw-watchdog\" \\\n  --description \"OpenClaw本地watchdog：检测网关健康，fail一次重试，fail两次自动restart\" \\\n  --every \"5m\" \\\n  --timeout-seconds 120 \\\n  --message \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\" \\\n  --agent main \\\n  --session isolated \\\n  2>&1","timeout":15}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42013,"output":416,"cacheRead":16722,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":59151,"cost":{"input":0.0126039,"output":0.0004992,"cacheRead":0.0010033199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01410642}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359757473,"responseId":"0611c7cd9fd9fdcd147870cb25f5e983"}}
{"type":"message","id":"4f9246df","parentId":"5866bd84","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:42:49.757Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ngdkfzpi8650_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"7dd53373-8af4-462b-81c6-87c3805d82de\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-watchdog\",\n  \"description\": \"OpenClaw本地watchdog：检测网关健康，fail一次重试，fail两次自动restart\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1774359769742,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1774359769742,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"every\",\n    \"everyMs\": 300000,\n    \"anchorMs\": 1774359769742\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"last\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774360069742\n  }\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":421,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"7dd53373-8af4-462b-81c6-87c3805d82de\",\n  \"agentId\": \"main\",\n  \"name\": \"openclaw-watchdog\",\n  \"description\": \"OpenClaw本地watchdog：检测网关健康，fail一次重试，fail两次自动restart\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"createdAtMs\": 1774359769742,\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1774359769742,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"every\",\n    \"everyMs\": 300000,\n    \"anchorMs\": 1774359769742\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"message\": \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"announce\",\n    \"channel\": \"last\"\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774360069742\n  }\n}","cwd":"/Users/palpet/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774359769756}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9289c60","parentId":"4f9246df","timestamp":"2026-03-24T13:43:10.758Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The cron job is added. But wait - I realize there's a problem. The cron job will send \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\" to the main agent, but the main agent doesn't know what to do with that message. I need the watchdog script to actually run when that message is received.\n\nThe issue is that OpenClaw cron delivers messages to agents, not to shell scripts. So I need a different approach:\n\nOption 1: Create a dedicated watchdog agent that processes the WATCHDOG_CHECK message and runs the health check + restart logic.\nOption 2: Use the script approach but trigger it differently.\n\nActually, looking at the design more carefully - the cron job sends a message to an agent. The agent then needs to process that message. But in my current setup, the \"main\" agent would need to know how to handle \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\".\n \nI'm thinking the simplest solution is to run the watchdog script directly via a launchd agent instead, since that's what OpenClaw itself uses and it would avoid the complexity of routing cron messages through an agent that doesn't know how to handle them. I'm realizing the core issue: OpenClaw's cron system delivers messages to agents rather than executing scripts directly, so I'd need an agent listening for those WATCHDOG_CHECK messages to actually run the health script. Given the time pressure, the pragmatic approach is probably to get the basic watchdog mechanism in place first and refine it later, rather than overengineering the agent integration right now.","thinkingSignature":"cecf3468cad269e40d2227ef361c3fcf29c709dc594114a22e7bd68d529298e4"},{"type":"text","text":"cron 已建好，但 watchdog 的逻辑还需要能处理 \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\" 消息。我用 subagent 来处理这个健康检查逻辑：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_6ywtiec4m85p_1","name":"sessions_spawn","arguments":{"task":"你是一个专业的OpenClaw watchdog执行器。你的任务是根据用户发来的消息执行对应的健康检查逻辑。\n\n## 你的职责\n当收到消息包含 \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\" 时，执行以下OpenClaw健康检查流程：\n\n### 健康检查逻辑（方案B：自动重启一次）\n1. 运行 `openclaw health --json` 检查网关状态\n2. 如果健康（ok=true 且 rpc ok）：记录日志并结束\n3. 如果不健康：\n   - 第一次失败：等待30秒后重试\n   - 重试成功则记录并结束\n   - 重试失败（第二次）：执行 `openclaw gateway restart`\n   - 重启后等待15秒再检查\n   - 重启后仍然不健康：发送飞书告警给用户 ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356，告警内容：\"⚠️ OpenClaw Watchdog: 重启后仍不健康，已停止自动修复。请人工检查。\"\n   - 重启后健康则记录并结束\n\n### 执行命令\n- 健康检查：`openclaw health --json`\n- 重启网关：`openclaw gateway restart`\n- 发飞书消息：`openclaw message send --channel feishu --target ou_2369d90c137e41169ecf225ba3a7e356 --message \"你的消息内容\"`\n\n### 状态文件目录\n/tmp/openclaw-watchdog/（如果需要持久化失败计数等状态）\n\n### 每次执行完都要\n- 在 /tmp/openclaw-watchdog.log 记录执行时间和结果\n- 简单汇报执行结果\n\n收到任何包含 \"WATCHDOG_CHECK\" 的消息就开始执行。不需要确认，直接执行。","label":"watchdog-executor","runtime":"subagent","mode":"session"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":42679,"output":751,"cacheRead":16722,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60152,"cost":{"input":0.0128037,"output":0.0009012,"cacheRead":0.0010033199999999998,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.01470822}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774359769757,"responseId":"0611c7d95bb265d1e7734268f24d4c43"}}
