{"type":"message","id":"f6a1cd4e","parentId":"5b7c9171","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:28:51.291Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to enable message reading permissions for the Feishu bot. Let me first check what permissions are currently available, and then figure out how to enable message reading.\n\nActually, looking at the Feishu tools available, I don't see a \"read messages\" tool. The Feishu tools I have are:\n- feishu_chat: chat operations (members, info, member_info)\n- feishu_doc: document operations\n- feishu_wiki: wiki operations\n- feishu_drive: drive operations\n- feishu_bitable: bitable operations\n- feishu_app_scopes: list current app permissions\n\n\n- feishu_chat: chat operations (members, info, member_info)\n\nNone of these provide message reading capabilities. It seems this isn't just a permission issue—the current toolset simply doesn't have message reading functionality available at all. I should clarify this limitation with the user rather than attempting something that isn't supported.","thinkingSignature":"11bde8cf7dad07ff5b5f167ddf05574214b5ec3abadcb2be8b9eaf97d1534682"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_b28rnq2jr6ug_1","name":"feishu_app_scopes","arguments":{}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":99,"output":219,"cacheRead":67061,"cacheWrite":213,"totalTokens":67592,"cost":{"input":0.0000297,"output":0.0002628,"cacheRead":0.004023659999999999,"cacheWrite":0.000079875,"total":0.0043960349999999995}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774362523023,"responseId":"0611d29b2f335898f0ce374518e09be8"}}
