{"type":"message","id":"c7821696","parentId":"19984235","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:59:38.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying that even the dialog box shouldn't pop up. The watchdog cron was returning messages to the conversation, and even with `--no-deliver` it seems like it's still somehow delivering to the conversation. \n\nWait - the watchdog check is sending results to the conversation via the subagent's session. The user is seeing these messages in the chat. Even with `--no-deliver` on the cron level, the subagent session itself might be configured to deliver results back to the main session.\n\nI need to either:\n1. Disable the watchdog cron entirely for the night\n2. Or reconfigure the subagent session to not send results back\n\nThe simplest thing to do right now would be to just disable the watchdog cron for now, since the user is going to sleep and doesn't want any interruptions at all.\n\nLet me disable the watchdog cron.","thinkingSignature":"b68d43acaf336ba50b97f7d2d4b84f5d6352edc3ad2ebe27caa3d623e2984b46"},{"type":"text","text":"\n[[reply_to_current]] 对，这个对话框也不该弹。直接关掉最省事：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yhorobp9zgmh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"openclaw cron disable 7dd53373-8af4-462b-81c6-87c3805d82de 2>&1","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":80,"output":257,"cacheRead":83504,"cacheWrite":1188,"totalTokens":85029,"cost":{"input":0.000024,"output":0.00030839999999999996,"cacheRead":0.005010239999999999,"cacheWrite":0.0004455,"total":0.005788139999999999}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774367971457,"responseId":"0611e7e3e9f0aeef2813a13b78a9a349"}}
